name: CPI
summary: Inflationary pressures in the US economy continued to intensify in March, exceeding expectations and casting doubts on the likelihood of near-term interest rate cuts by the Federal Reserve. The Consumer Price Index (CPI) surged by 3.5% year-over-year, its highest level since March 2012, and core CPI, which excludes volatile food and energy prices, also rose significantly. This stubborn inflation has raised concerns among experts and economists, who believe it may force the Fed to delay its plans for rate cuts. The unexpected inflation report has dashed hopes for a dovish turn by the central bank, as it now faces increasing pressure to address rising price pressures. This is especially pertinent considering the Fed's dual mandate of price stability and maximum employment. The sustained inflation, if left unchecked, poses significant risks to the economy in the long run.

name: DJ Mister Cee
summary: The music industry is mourning the loss of renowned DJ Mister Cee, who passed away at the age of 57. Mister Cee, also known as Calvin LeBrun, was a pioneer in Brooklyn's hip-hop scene, serving as Big Daddy Kane's DJ and contributing as a producer for Notorious B.I.G. Tributes poured in from the likes of 50 Cent, DJ Premier, and Chuck D, highlighting his significant contribution to hip-hop. His legacy was celebrated with a special tribute show on SiriusXM, while media outlets such as The New York Times, Rolling Stone, and Pitchfork covered his life and impact on the music world. Mister Cee's death leaves a void in the New York City DJ scene, where he was known for his groundbreaking work and mentorship of aspiring artists.

name: Allen Weisselberg
summary: Former Trump Organization CFO Allen Weisselberg has been sentenced to five months in jail for perjury. Weisselberg pleaded guilty to lying about the size of a Trump triplex apartment during the Trump civil fraud trial. The sentence is a significant development in the ongoing legal cases against the Trump Organization and its associates. Weisselberg's sentencing comes after he testified that he intentionally misstated the size of the apartment in order to reduce Trump's property taxes. The prosecution argued that Weisselberg's actions were part of a broader scheme to defraud the government. The sentencing is a setback for the Trump Organization, which is facing a number of other legal challenges, including a criminal investigation into its financial practices.

name: Tara VanDerveer
summary: After coaching the Stanford Cardinal women's basketball team for 38 seasons, Tara VanDerveer announced her retirement. As the NCAA's winningest coach, VanDerveer led Stanford to three national championships, 13 Final Four appearances, and 23 Pac-12 regular seasons and tournament titles. VanDerveer explained her decision, stating that she simply felt ready to step away. Her retirement has been met with praise and recognition, with many acknowledging her exceptional career and contributions to the sport.

name: FISA
summary: The Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act (FISA) is facing opposition from House Republicans, who have been vocal in their criticism of the measure. President Trump has also been critical of FISA, calling for it to be "killed." In a recent procedural vote, the House failed to pass a motion to reauthorize FISA, in a setback for the GOP. The conservative wing of the House is leading the opposition to FISA, blocking efforts to renew its key provisions. As a result, the House has struck down the FISA renewal, leaving the future of this surveillance program uncertain. Some lawmakers believe that FISA should be reauthorized without a warrant requirement, while others argue that it is an essential tool for intelligence gathering.

summary: The Detroit Red Wings are facing playoff contention with five games remaining. Their recent win over the Buffalo Sabres, despite a hot start from Buffalo, has kept their hopes alive. Despite a missed high-sticking call, Andrew Copp suffered a broken cheekbone, casting a shadow on the team's prospects. The game against the Sabres also raised questions as to why the Red Wings continued shooting at the empty net at the end of the game. The Rangers-Red Wings game on Friday will be a pivotal contest, with both teams vying for playoff spots. The Red Wings' playoff destiny is in their own hands, and they will need more production from Alex DeBrincat to secure a berth.

name: Jrue Holiday
summary: Boston Celtics guard Jrue Holiday has reportedly agreed to a four-year, $135 million contract extension with the team. The deal, which is pending a physical, will keep Holiday in Boston through the 2026-27 season. Holiday, a two-time All-Star, was acquired by the Celtics in a trade with the New Orleans Pelicans in February 2020. He has been a key contributor for the Celtics, averaging 19.7 points, 6.3 rebounds, and 6.8 assists per game during the regular season. Holiday has also played a significant role in the Celtics' success in the playoffs, helping the team reach the Eastern Conference Finals in both 2020 and 2021.
